name: St James Episcopal Preschool
detail: Each child is a unique creation of God.  Young children are curious by nature.  They are excited and eager to participate in activities that encourage hands-on experiences.  The environment at our preschool is safe, positive, and supportive.  We believe in offering full and rich opportunities to develop in each child a love for God, self-esteem, responsibility, and a readiness for life long-learning that is appropriate to each child.

name: ST Jerome Little Lions Learning Center
detail:
Little Lions Learning Center (LLLC) is a faith-based preschool that supports the cognitive, social, emotional, physical, and spiritual development of young children.

Little Lions Learning Center strives to develop the faith, mind, and body of its students through a high quality education in a secure and nuturing environment that fosters the development of the whole child through play-based learning.

Your child will feel at home in one of Little Lions Learning Center's small classes.  Little Lions Learning Center has a low student to teacher ratio so your child will not feel lost in the crowd, but instead receive individualized attention from his or her teacher.

name: St Johns Methodist School For Little Children
detail:
Since its inception 40 years ago in 1973, St. John’s School for Little Children has striven to provide children with high quality academic instruction in a very accepting, loving, Christian environment.  

It is our intent that the Little School program helps prepare your child for success in school and in life.  What is our goal for your child?  To become an independent, responsible human being with a great desire and ability to learn, question, communicate, and to function in a social setting.   We believe these traits serve them throughout their lives.  We try to accomplish this through the activities we plan, the way we organize the classrooms, select developmentally appropriate toys and materials, plan daily schedules, and talk with children.

name: ST Luke Christian Child Development Center
detail: St. Luke Christian Child Development Center is a ministry of St. Luke United Methodist Church.  As an outreach to the community, it is designed to provide young children with creative and Christ centered learning experiences that promote good self image and self acceptance. The center offers children and their families an atmosphere of love in which children are allowed to develop social, motor, verbal, academic and spiritual skills at their own maturation level.

name: ST Luke Methodist DC
detail:
Looking for a preschool for your child?  St. Luke United Methodist Church offers preschool classes for children ages 2-kindergarten.

At St. Luke Preschool your child will be taught age appropriate curriculum, with social skills such as sharing, playing with others, manners, and taking turns.  In addition to classroom instruction, each class has scheduled outside play time each days as the weather permits.

Hours of class instruction are from 8 – 11:30am, Monday through Friday with early drop off and afternoon care offered for an additional fee.

The school year follows the Ysleta School District Calendar, although there are a few days each year that Ysleta gives students off that the St. Luke Pre-school is in session.

If you would like more information, or would like to register your child please contact the Preschool director Cindy Jury at 591-8126, or stop by in person at St. Luke UMC 9915 Montwood Dr, across from Eastwood High School.Get your child enrolled in a program where they will have a great time learning with other children!

name: ST Luke the Evangelist Early Childhood Center
detail:
The mission of St. Luke the Evangelist's Early Childhood Center is to maximize your child’s potential by providing hands on materials, dedicated teachers, personalized curriculum and life long skills to cultivate your child’s intellectual, physical, and social development in a safe and loving Christian environment.

We offer a 5 day program for 18 months to 3 year olds, as well as a Pre-K 5 day program with all times being from 9-2 p.m. daily. Space is limited.

name: ST Lukes Child Development Program
detail: Our Child Development Program is licensed by the Texas Department of Protective & Regulatory Services and meets or exceeds all the standards of a licensed day care center. We are licensed to care for children from 6 weeks to the age of 12 years.
business hours:
Monday - Friday from 
7:00 am to 6:00 pm

name: ST Mark Pre School
detail: The mission of St. Mark Preschool and Child Care is to provide safe, quality care for children in a joyful Christian environment that provides learning and self worth.

name: St Marks United Methodist Church Daycare Center
St Paul Parents Day Out
detail: At the Saint Paul "Parents Day Out" program, we strive to provide a safe Christ-centered environment in which children ages 2, 3, and 4 years old can grow in their social, physical, and spiritual development while having lots of FUN! Class assignment is determined by age as of September 1 of the current school year.

name: ST Paul Christian Learning Center
detail: St. Paul Christian Learning Center helps children grow in a learning and caring Christian environment.  Our aim is to give quality care while stimulating young minds.

name: St Paul Lutheran Church and School
St Paul Lutheran Creative CC
detail:
We minister to families with young children by providing an excellent school in a Christian atmosphere of love, acceptance, and respect. Our 
goal is to foster the development of the whole child in these aspects: 
physical, spiritual, emotional, and intellectual.

name: St Paul Presbyterian Early Childhood
detail: For nearly 50 years, our program has focused on a child’s natural curiosity as a way to build a strong educational base. We maintain an atmosphere of play and fun with positive reinforcement and age-appropriate curricula and activities – all in a loving, Christian environment that builds the child’s self-esteem. Our low student-to-teacher ratios ensure a safe and nurturing environment.

name: St Paul's Lutheran Church After School Program
detail: On Monday, March 31, 2008 we opened our After School Program.  This free program will bring new life to more than 35 kids from our neighborhood as well as to their families.  New life that will mean a safe place for the kids to go after school where there will be caring  people to help with homework and to teach new skills.  New life that may mean exposure to the gospel of Jesus for the first time.   The children have chapel time once a week in the sanctuary with Bible lesson, prayers, and music.

name: ST Pauls Mornings with Jesus Catholic Early Education
detail: Our Mission is to provide children with the best possible opportunity to connect within and learn about God’s world in a loving, safe and spiritual setting.

name: St Peter Lutheran Preschool
detail: St. Peter Lutheran Preschool, a ministry of St. Peter Lutheran Church, is a non-profit organization sponsored by St. Peter Lutheran Church. St. Peter Lutheran Church and Preschool are both members of the Lutheran Church-Missouri Synod. St. Peter Lutheran Preschool is called to provide a Christ-centered, first-school experience for children, while developing their love for learning and celebrating their individual uniqueness.

name: St Philips Methodist Discover Club
detail: Have you ever heard of the DISCOVERY SCHOOL? It's a day school ministry of St. Philip's United Methodist Church that provides very young children the opportunity to learn, play, and enjoy the company of other children in a safe, nurturing environment that reflects God's love.

name: St Phillip's Preschool
detail: St. Philip’s Preschool operates a state-licensed preschool program for children ages 2-5 year olds. Our purpose is to provide a preschool program in which each child can grow and develop spiritually, cognitively, physically, emotionally and socially within a Christian atmosphere. We believe each child is a child of God—a special unique person valued for his/her own worth, who is growing and learning at his/her own pace as he/she actively relates to our world through play—- a child’s “work.” We believe that this program is one of the church’s outreaches into our community as we strive to meet the needs of children and encourage participation and education.

name: ST Stephens Preschool
detail: St. Stephen's Episcopal School, a coeducational boarding and day school of the Diocese of Texas, is a caring, diverse community, inclusive of all faiths and grounded in the Christian tradition, which nurtures moral growth and values the potential and dignity of every human being. We challenge motivated students to live intelligently, creatively and humanely as contributing members of society. We develop the whole person by providing rigorous academic preparation, stimulating physical activities and rich opportunities in the fine arts.

name: ST Thomas More Preschool
detail: St. Thomas More is very proud of its Preschool program which is designed to be an extension of the family. Our program has been carefully developed for the enrichment of the whole child within a loving, Catholic environment. We give special attention to the developmental stages, skills and needs of our children, while encouraging and nurturing each child’s God-given talents. Our goal is to make preschool a positive, rewarding and fun, growing experience for the child; intellectually, physically, emotionally, socially, and spiritually. - See more at: http://stmaustin.org/st-thomas-more-preschool#sthash.WpMGOnnp.dpuf

name: St. Andrews CDC
detail:
Our MDO program emphasizes hands-on, developmentally appropriate play experiences. Blue Roof School has carefully planned to provide quality Christian child care. We recognize the uniqueness of each child and provide for individualized experiences to help children reach their maximum potential. At Blue Roof School, the children are given the opportunity to:

    Develop decision-making practices by selecting activities from a variety of learning centers
    Express themselves creatively through open-ended art, music, dramatic play, and the use of unstructured materials
    Experience positive, loving interactions with children and adults
    Verbalize feelings in a supportive, accepting environment that encourages independence and self-control
    Participate in and enjoy language experiences
    Develop fine and gross motor skills and participate in physical activities
    Practice proper bathroom function and hygiene (a.k.a. - potty training)

This program focuses attention on language development, large motor skills use and mastery, and social development. The MDO daily schedule is developed to meet the needs for balanced active and quiet play times, large and small group interaction, and indoor and outdoor activities.

name: St. Clare of Assisi Preschool and Mother's Day Out
St. Georges & St. Patricks Episcopal School
St. John Bosco Child Development Center
detail:
Welcome to St. John Bosco Child Development Center (CDC). Our staff is dedicated to providing your child with the finest care possible. In following St. John Bosco’s teachings, our center focuses on all aspects of your child’s development.

Our mission is to educate youth and form them spiritually in the Salesian tradition of Reason, Religion, and Loving Kindness.  All of us at St. John Bosco School and Development Center work together to help make St. John Bosco a place where children love to learn and learn to love.

name: St. John Lutheran Parochial Day Care
St. Joseph Catholic School Early Learning Center
detail:
St. Joseph Catholic School, (located at 2307 South Garrett Street since 1963), has served the Marshall community and surrounding Harrison County area with quality education since 1879 with two previous temporary closings to its final closing in 2001 due to area economic distress. The school experienced re-opeing in 2007 as an Early Learning Center, now known as "Pre-Kindergarten."
 
Pre-Kindergarten classes enroll children ages 3-4 years. They are taught by teachers who are attentive, energetic, and love teaching these youngest students. The “Pre-K” classes are education curriculum-based and prepare children academically and socially for the expectations of Kindergarten, 1st grade and beyond.
 
The school continually strengthens its identity as a Catholic school. It is an accredited elementary school, currently having academic offerings to 4th grade with extraordinary student achievement and provides another education choice for parents in our growing Marshall community and surrounding area.
 
Parents have chosen St. Joseph’s Catholic School for their children’s education because of its safe, Christ-centered environment, academic excellence, and attentive enthusiastic teachers. From baking pies to planting a garden, our students are learning to apply math and science in everyday things. Social studies and important communication skills such as reading, writing, and public speaking are part of the curriculum. Spanish language, music and art are also offered and participation in physical education is a vital activity that is important to the enrichment and overall learning development of each child.

St. Joseph's has a library with over 2,000 age-appropriate offerings and is a place for students to study and enjoy special reading programs.
 
In addition to academic studies, our students are learning about kindness and respect for themselves and others by practicing the disciplines of patience and sharing Christian values such as loving our neighbors as Jesus taught.
 
We encourage you to visit our school and witness for yourselves what wonderful miracles take place on a daily basis that we know as “truth in action” that only children can experience. - See more at: http://www.sjcsm.org/index.cfm?load=page&page=154#sthash.jSgmlxka.dpuf

name: St. Joseph Eagles Nest on Preston
St. Laurence Weekday Children's Program
detail: St. Laurence Weekday Children's Program is an Early Childhood ministry of St. Laurence Parish. We believe that children are the heart of the Kingdom of God. Together with family and community we are called to support children’s spiritual and human growth and development.

name: St. Mark's Catholic Preschool and Nursery
detail:
St. Mark’s Catholic School provides a nurturing environment in a caring and positive atmosphere to create a warm and happy place for children to learn. As we bridge the gap from home to school, we guide children to a continued good selfimage while building social skills in a school setting.

Sensory, motor, perceptual and language skills are introduced through materials and activities, which are both child-centered and teacher directed. Work is planned which emphasizes the process rather than the product, fostering a sense of accomplishment and pride.

In that children’s learning begins by exploring the world around them through tactile experiences, students will foster creativity, develop independence, enhance curiosity and expand social skills.

Each child will be respected as an individual with his or her own timetable and learning style. Through listening, questioning and making choices, the child will learn to enjoy the process of learning and find joy in his or her own achievements.

St. Mark’s fosters an “open door” policy and welcomes parents to visit the classroom and the office.

name: St. Monica's Mini Academy Day Care Center
detail: The mission of St. Monica Catholic School is to provide all students a challenging academic curriculum within a program where Catholic values reflecting God's love are taught, practiced, and ever present.

name: St. Paul's Lutheran Child Development Center
St. Philip's College Child Development Center
detail:
The St. Philip's College Child Development Center (CDC) is committed to providing the community quality child care and development. CDC professionals remain current in leading child development techniques, such as hand-on experience, authentic learning, and peer interaction.

The CDC is children-centered and responsive to cultural, ethnical, and socio-economic diversity. We pride ourselves in our ability to teach children of all backgrounds, capabilities, and educational opportunities.

name: St. Rita's Mother's Day Out
detail: The mission of St. Rita Catholic School, a parish community school, is to educate children in accordance with the educational ministry of the Catholic Church. We strive to foster spiritual, intellectual, physical, and social growth within each child to become a witness to Christian values as a member of our global community. As a part of this, the School invites parents to become active participants in their children's education since they are, as the Church affirms, the primary educators of their children.

name: St. Thomas Episcopal School
detail: The mission of St. Thomas Episcopal School is to help children achieve individual excellence by educating them in a developmentally based program where they may grow cognitively, physically, socially, emotionally, and spiritually.

name: Star Kids Education and Day Care Center
Star Montessori School
detail: “Star Montessori School” provides a nurturing and conceptual learning environment that encourages the growth of self-esteem, creativity, imagination with math, reading and writing skill to children of age from 6 weeks to 6 years in highly accredited Montessori curriculum. The goal of this school is to provide highest quality care with educational skill development in a conceptual nurturing environment which helps every child to develop fully to his/her intellectual, physical, emotional and social potential. Children learn the most by freedom of choice, independence and age appropriate activities under appropriate environment setup with positive guidance from the caregiver. The learning environment is set up to address and respond to the child’s changing needs from infant to kindergarten which guides the child to be logical thinkers, problem solvers, clear writers, thoughtful reader, and skillful computer users.
business hours:
Monday - Friday 6:30AM to 6:15PM for Toddler And PreK
Monday - Friday 7:30AM to 6:15PM for Infant.

name: Star of Hope - June Wagonner House of Hope
StarKids Academy
detail:
"At StarKids, our primary goal is for children to feel safe and secure. Additionally, we believe that 
a  learning  environment which fosters respect for cultural diversity and utilizes an eclectic approach 
to education allows for optimal growth and development of young children.  Young children's developmental tasks are to 
build trust, learn social skills, begin mastery of academic skills and develop positive self-esteem. And, in order to best support these tasks, our program strives to provide developmental appropriate activities, well-trained and consistent staff, a safe and healthy learning environment, and continuity of care. Also, we believe parents   are their child's first teacher; thus, we work to support parents in their efforts to guide their child's development."

name: Start Smart Academy # 2
detail: Welcome to our program. The goal of Start Smart Academy is to provide the child with an environment that will promote his or her bi-social, psychosocial and cognitive development. We believe that we have a responsibility to provide a caring, nurturing, learning environment that will enhance children’s social, emotional, physical, and cognitive development. Children are individuals with unique personalities and our job is to treat them with respect and dignity. We believe that open communication between the parent and the center creates a partnership that works together to instill appropriate values, morals and self-confidence within the child. An atmosphere of love and caring surrounds our infants. Their sensory development and perception are stimulated by their interactions with the teachers. Our Toddlers thrive in a program that introduces young children to early language skills, social interaction, cooperation and beginning educational concepts. Our Three and Four Year Olds are taught beginning reading skills and number concepts through age appropriateactivities. Our School-age tutoring program provides guidance while students do their homework. Students are encouraged to use problem solving skills and their creative abilities to develop arts and crafts, games, cooking activities etc. The program has written curriculum plans based on knowledge of child development and assessment of individual needs and interests. The learning environment and activities for children reflect the program’s philosophy and goals. Start Smart is prohibited from discriminating on the basis of race, color, sex, age, handicap, religion, disability, political beliefs or national origin. The center has an Open Door Policy and parents are welcome at all times WITHOUT PRIOR APPROVAL.

name: Starting Small
detail: Starting Small Child Development Center is dedicated to enriching the lives of your little ones and preparing them for the days ahead.

name: State Line Early Childhood Learning Academy
Steady Steps Childrens Weekday Ministry
detail: Steady Steps Children's Weekday Ministry has been established to serve young children and their parents in our wonderful community. Our mission is to provide a comprehensive, quality, christian program which fosters spiritual, emotional, cognitive and physical growth for all children who enroll. Through our sliding scale fee schedule, we are able to provide quality care for families at all income levels. Steady Steps operates under the guidance and authority of the Steady Steps council, which is comprised of 9 individuals from the community, plus the director. These individuals are FUMC members, teachers, Steady Steps parents, and others. The Steady Steps council meets once a month.

name: Stephenville Early Head Start
detail: The mission of Texas Neighborhood Services is found in its chartered by-laws originally created in 1965 and modified throughout the corporation’s history. The chartered mission is to administer the social programs of the United States, State, Public or Private assignment or award in the various counties applied for and to administer other programs designed to assist citizens in the counties we serve. Texas Neighborhood Services strategically targets this mission with the support of three significant groups in the community; representatives of the low-income, elected officials from the public sector, and business leaders from the private sector. The objective of working with these groups is to seek out, identify, and aid in the elimination of the causes of poverty within the communities served, help people prepare for, find and retain long term employment, and match employers with a quality, job-ready workforce. TNS executes this mission to make the entire community more responsive to the needs and interests of its citizens. This is accomplished by mobilizing available resources and bringing about a greater institutional sensitivity to the individuals being helped while at the same time developing a system of priorities among projects, activities, and areas, as needed, for the most effective and efficient use of resources.

name: Stepping Stone School
detail: For 46 years Stepping Stone School has served over 15,000 families in the Tyler and East Texas area and continues to be an exemplary school where students love to learn and where a strong emphasis upon a dynamic, rigorous, proven curriculum and character development is taught by outstanding teachers. Stepping Stone offers one continuous program of high educational quality from infants through Pre-K and welcomes students from diverse religious, ethnic, and socioeconomic backgrounds.

name: Stepping Stone School
detail:
Stepping Stone School is a comprehensive early care and education program that profoundly nurtures children and prepares them for lifelong happiness. This means:

    Your child will be nurtured toward confidence, social success, academic achievement and school readiness.
    Your child will be safe in a clean, organized and educational environment.
    The teacher-child and teacher-parent relationships will complement your parent-child relationship.
    You will enjoy a trusted partnership with your child’s principal and teachers.

The Stepping Stone School experience will promote your child’s sense of belonging, as well as ensure healthy cognitive, physical and social-emotional development. Our goal is to exceed your expectations!

name: Stepping Stones
detail: At Stepping Stones we want to provide you with the highest quality care for your child possible and the best education. The very best education may not be the lowest cost but it is definitely the best value. Please call us today to set up an appointment to see our school and get your child started on the path to success!

name: Stepping Stones in Development CCC
detail: When your child stays with us, you can rest assured knowing our state-licensed facility is providing him or her with the utmost care. Our staff is CPR and first-aid certified with annual training programs to provide the absolute best care for your child. With over 30 years experience, owner Sheryl Burleson has been providing top-notch child care to the Wichita Falls area. Our curriculum focuses on cognitive, emotional, social and religious development give your child a well-rounded background.

name: Stepping Stones Learning Center II
detail:
Stepping Stones Learning Centers are child care centers in Pearland, and offer a pre-school curriculum to meet all your child’s needs. Stepping Stones I & II are enrolling children 6 weeks to 12 years. Both offer a before and after school program during the regular school year, for school-aged children. They also offer a fun filled summer program for pre-school and school-aged children.

We offer two convenient locations for Pearland families. The original location (Stepping Stones Learning Center I) is located near central Pearland, just north of the Dad’s Club Sports Park, on FM 518. Our newest location (Stepping Stones Learning Center II) is located near Cullen Blvd, and is perfect for parents located in Southdown, Silverlake or Shadow Creek Ranch.

Pricillia Jones is the owner of Stepping Stones Learning Centers.  She has a long history in the child care business, and uses a hands-on approach to managing both locations. Stepping Stones Learning Centers have a long history of a extremely positive rating with Texas State Child Care Licensing.

Stepping Stones Child Care Centers are members of the Pearland Chamber of Commerce and the Child Care Licensing Association.

name: Stepping Stones of Knowledge Academy Inc
detail: Our mission is to provide a safe and nurturing environment where your child can gain the academic and social skills needed to help them reach their potential one step at a time.

name: Strickland After School
detail:
Building Christian Character

1.    We believe in one eternal, omniscient and omnipresent God who reveals Himself personally as Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. He is a God of love and truth who has created the universe and given man dominion over the whole earth.

2.    Man has fallen from fellowship and communion with God due to sin and rebellion, and is incapable of restoring that fellowship through his own works because of his total depravity and separation from God.

3.    Jesus Christ is the incarnate Son of God, and was sent by God to destroy the works of the devil and redeem mankind from sin and its effects. He was born of a virgin, lived a sinless life, was crucified, died, and was buried. He rose from the dead bodily and ascended into heaven. His death was the substitutionary punishment for man's sin and His blood is the only means of purification from sin. As both God and man He is the only mediator between God and men and the only Savior of the world; He will return to earth to judge all men.

4.    God commands all men everywhere to repent, believe in the Lord Jesus and be baptized for the remission of their sins.

5.    Man is saved by grace through faith in Jesus Christ and in His gospel only. All men will be resurrected to judgment by God. Those who are lost will pay the penalty of eternal damnation, and those who are saved will be rewarded with eternal life and joy in God's presence.

6.    God has sent the Holy Spirit to dwell in men, to renew and regenerate men, and to guide them into all the truth.

7.    The Bible is the inspired, inerrant Word of God and is therefore our authority for faith and action. Studying and meditating on the Scriptures is valuable for learning the truth, correcting wrong thinking and actions, and training in godliness and righteous living.

8.    Jesus Christ is the Lord and only sovereign of our lives, so we must honor, worship, and obey Him, and do all that He has commanded to accomplish His purposes and establish His kingdom on the earth.

9.    Children are a heritage and gift from the Lord to their parents. Parents, and most especially the father, therefore are the authority and responsible parties in the training, discipline, admonition, and care of their children. We believe the school is called by God to assist the parents and minister to the children so that youth may take their place in the family, church, and society as God has intended.

name: Suburban Child Care Center
detail:
Our curriculum is presented through the use of themes that include Home, Family & Pets, Community Helpers, Native Americans, Our Senses, Nutrition, Our Bodies, Safety, Plant Life, Insects, Dinosaurs and many others. WE strive to positively challenge the children that attend our school and to help them develop interests at our learning center that will help prepare them for our ever changing and complex world. We see each child as an individual and encourage self-expression, independence, and responsibility. By having a higher standard of quality childcare in a unique setting and always being mindful of children’s growth and development Suburban School makes every effort to strengthen your child’s consciousness.

Being in a social setting helps you child to create connections, develop communication skills and learn to problem-solve. As your child moves through our program, learning centers, curriculum themes, and activities they become more sophisticated. Your child’s skills continue to develop by building upon prior knowledge and experiences. Suburban School has a large variety of quality resources, and we are continually reviewing and updating our curriculum and materials.

In addition to providing an enriched curriculum that is substantiated by portfolios, progress reports, and an annual developmental assessment, our Curriculum Coordinator is certified to administer and evaluate the Gesell Developmental Screening Tool. Our learning center and school curriculum is also enhanced through our outdoor environment which consists of numerous play and experiential areas; this positively effects brain development. With six wooded acres all of our students can be in an outdoor setting at the same time. The indoor environment is designed to be as homelike as possible to provide a secure and comforting atmosphere. Depending on the time of year in San Antonio and the age of the child, Children are served a morning snack, a nutritional lunch, and afternoon snacks in their classroom or outside on picnic tables. Cooking projects are included as part of the curriculum as well.

We strongly support a cooperative relationship between home and school. Along with informal communication, we enable this by incorporating additional opportunities to help keep parents informed and involved in their child’s progress. In September we have a Parent’s Afternoon to talk about the expectations for the school year. In December we have an Open House. In January we begin our Parent/Teacher conferences. Monthly, parents receive a calendar that details the themes, concepts, developmental skills and activities that are being presented. These are developed from the lead teacher’s lesson plans, which they prepare and reflects the school’s curriculum. Teachers also send home a monthly newsletter to share with parents some of the special moments that have occurred during class activities and to give insight into your child’s world at school.

name: Sugar Creek Baptist Mothers Day Out
Sugar Creek Childrens House
detail:
Sugar Creek Montessori school’s mission is to provide a safe, positive and nurturing environment that develops the ‘whole child’ and inculcates:
-Respect for self and others
-Positive learning attitude and habits
-Emotional, social and intellectual competencies
-Creativity and innovative learning skills
-Universal human values
-Leadership potential

name: Sugarland Head Start
detail: W.S.S. Tri-County Child Development Council, Inc. believes that by empowering the families to meet the needs of their children while striving toward self-sufficiency, provides the family with the greatest opportunity of long-term success. W.S.S. Tri-County Child Development Council, Inc. believes that by empowering the communities to be more aware of and responsive to the disadvantages of day to day living faced by low income families will provide the greatest likelihood for the prevention of poverty. W.S.S. Tri-County Child Development Council, Inc. believes that through effective collaboration family members will be afforded the opportunity to access comprehensive services that when sustained over a sufficient period of time will initiate real and meaningful differences in the lives of children and their families.

name: Summit Private School
detail:
Summit Private School has been owned and operated by Robyn Johnson & Shannon Kovitch since 1997. Both are former public school teachers. Robyn has a degree in Elementary Education with an Early Childhood Specialization. She also earned her Masters degree in Educational Administration with a Mid-management certificate. Shannon has a BS in Home Economics with a teacher certification. Together they have over 30 years of experience working with children.

Summit Private School is involved with Child Care Services Rising Star School Program. Summit has continuously earned the highest rating of 4 Stars, since beginning the program in 2001.  This rating is based on evaluations that Summit receives over a year long process. The evaluation consists of day-long monitoring of the learning environment that includes ratios, curriculum and discipline.

Summit has a privately written curriculum for its preschool program. Children are actively involved in their learning environment. Rooms are arranged in specific center areas to provide optimal learning. Children are taught lessons each day that include mathematics and language arts. Summit also incorporates Sign Language and Spanish into the day.

name: Suncreek Childrens Development Center
detail: Suncreek Kids is a ministry of Suncreek United Methodist Church. We seek to provide learning opportunities for children in a safe and loving environment that are developmentally appropriate, intellectually stimulating and spiritually nurturing.

name: Sunnyview Head Start
detail: Head Start of Greater Dallas, Inc. provides children with the foundation of skills and knowledge they need to be successful in school and life and fosters self-reliant families and communities.

name: Sunrise Baptist Church-Lillie
detail: Lillie Hill offers Day Care services from birth to preschool. We have a summer program and an after school program as well. We also have various hands on activities with plenty of time to play is incorporated throughout each day. We are a bilingual facility: Spanish and English.

name: Sunrise Early Learning And Development Center
Sunset Canyon Baptist Church Preschool
detail: Welcome to Sunset Canyon Baptist Church Preschool! We are looking forward to sharing early learning experiences with your child, and we appreciate you choosing our program as a positive place for your child to grow and develop. Sunset Canyon Baptist Church Preschool is a ministry and outreach of our church, and our staff is committed to serving your child and family to the best of our ability.
business hours:
*18 months - 2 year old classes- Tues. and Thurs. from 8:30 a.m.- 1 p.m.
*3, 4 and 5 year old classes- Tues., Wed., Thurs. from 8:30 a.m.- 1 p.m.

name: Tanglewood Learning Center
detail:
Dr. Maria Montessori observed and studied the nature of the learning process in children. She believed that every child delights in spontaneous activity directed toward intellectual discovery. The carefully prepared environment of a Montessori classroom nourishes a child's natural development. Attitudes and confidence developed during the formative years will serve children throughout their lives. For a confident child, new activities are not only a challenge but also a delight. Children are most apt to retain a positive attitude toward learning and acquire confidence in a relaxed atmosphere where they set their own pace, follow their own interests and are free of criticism and competition. The following are some basic Montessori concepts:

    Children are respected as different from adults, and who differ from each other.
    Children possess unusual sensitivity and mental powers for absorbing and learning from the environment.
    The most important years of growth are the first years of life when unconscious learning is gradually brought to the conscious level.
    Children love work - it is spontaneously chosen and carried out with intense joy.
    Children need to learn by doing. At each stage in a child's mental growth, the Montessori curriculum provides activities that allow children to develop and refine their movements. The natural development of "I CAN DO IT MYSELF" is respected.
    Montessori methods reflect a profound respect for the child's personality. Children are allowed a large measure of liberty (not license) which forms the basis of real self-discipline. This is a higher discipline which originates within children as they practice making their own decisions and exercising their own will. It is not a discipline imposed on the child by a teacher or based on rewards or punishments.
business hours:
Full Day  6:30 am to 6:00 pm

name: Tanglewood-Clayton Child Care
detail:
Our curriculum is based on nine free choice stations that we call Exploration Stations that allow us to meet the needs of individual students in our afterschool program while still meeting the needs of the larger group. This concept gives children opportunities to make decisions and to evaluate the consequences of their choices, following the adage, “The best education is caught, not taught.”

It also allows them to use their time more effectively, rather than wasting time while waiting turns. In addition, it permits them to move about freely without interfering with other children’s activities. Perhaps most important, our Exploration Stations allow children to succeed in accomplishing tasks, mainly because they select the tasks they wish to accomplish.

detail: We believe that children have the right to a nurturing, safe environment where they can feel comfortable and secure. We recognize that each child is an individual and that each child must be allowed to develop at his or her own pace. name: The Happy Tree CDC
detail:
The story of The Happy Tree Child Development Center started in October of 1989.  The center was started by a young woman from Brooklyn, New York, who had just completed college at South Carolina State University in Early Child Development Education.  Frances Bennett, the only one of 19 children to complete her education, had an interest in the lives of young children so much so that she was led to open a high quality child development center.

Her first center was located on site at an apartment faculty in Far North Dallas during the late 80’s.  It grew from 17 to over 50 students.  The concept back then was to have high quality care where one lived.  This concept was a hit!

The childcare center continued to grow and was relocated to Carrollton in 1990.  The center enrolled over 130 students and was able to continue the success of the providing high quality care to families.   In 2001, the center grew yet again. This time we would relocate to our own building.

The moment you walk through the doors you can sense that you are in a place of caring, loving, respectful and patient individuals.  Here at the center, we take pride in providing children and families with the highest level of care and developmentally appropriate practice. Simply put, The Happy Tree is a home away from home. Our teachers are well equipped to take care of your children because of their full knowledge in Early Childhood Education.  We are devoted to rising healthy, happy, and intelligence children, because we put our heart and soul into it.

name: The Kangaroo Club
detail:
The philosophy behind our curriculum is that young children learn best by doing. Learning isn’t just repeating what someone else says; it requires active thinking and experimenting to find out how things work and to learn firsthand about the world we live in.

In their early years, children explore the world around them by using all their senses (touching, tasting, listening, smelling and looking). In using real materials such as blocks and trying out their ideas, children learn about sizes, shapes and colors, and they notice relationships between things.

Play provides the foundation of academic or “school” learning. It is the preparation children need before they learn highly abstract symbols such as letters (which are symbols for sounds) and numbers (which are symbols for number concepts). Play enables us to achieve the key goals of our early childhood curriculum. Play is the work of young children.

The most important goal of our early childhood curriculum is to help children become enthusiastic learners. This means encouraging children to be active and creative explorers who are not afraid to try out their ideas and to think their own thoughts.
Our curriculum identifies goals in all areas of development.

Social: 
To help children feel comfortable in school, trust their new environment, make friends and feel they are a part of the group.

Emotional:
To help children experience pride and self-confidence, develop independence and self-control and have a positive attitude toward life.

Cognitive: To help children become confident learners by letting them try out their own ideas and experience success, and by helping them acquire learning skills such as the ability to solve problems, ask questions and use words to describe their ideas, observations and feelings.

Physical:
To help children increase their large and small muscle skills and feel confident about what their bodies can do.

The activities we plan for children, the way we organize the environment, select toys and materials, plan the daily schedule and talk with children, are all designed to accomplish the goals of our curriculum and give your child a successful start in school.

Each classroom is set-up in a way that promotes exploration and has distinct areas of interest; each area is well defined and has a variety of materials and equipment.

The Infant Program curriculum at The Kangaroo Club is developmentally appropriate. We use specific guidelines for what activities are appropriate for each stage of development. Staff will also take into consideration each infant's individual personality, temperament, and stage of development. Lesson plans are individualized for each baby. Our daily program has activities that will allow your infant time to grow, as well as explore, experiment, discover and play. Our Infant Curriculum goals are as follows:

Infant Program
•To provide infants with many one-on-one, face-to-face interactions. All interactions are characterized by gentle and supportive responses 
•To foster infants with a positive identity, and sense of well-being by rocking, holding and cuddling 
•To allow infants to achieve mastery of their bodies through self-initiated motor skills such as rolling, sitting, standing, etc. 
•To encourage infants to think, reason, question and experiment.  One way to encourage this is to provide simple toys that respond to infant's initiations, so they may witness cause and effect 
•To encourage language and literacy development 
•To enhance physical development skills by allowing infants to move comfortably and by providing open carpeted areas and low, sturdy furniture 
•To provide regular outdoor experiences 
•To encourage creative expression through music, activities & art 
•To incorporate routine tasks such as eating, diapering, etc., as a means for furthering an infant's learning, self-help and social skills

Safety:  We know that concern for the safety of your child tops your list of things to consider when selecting a child care center. The Kangaroo Club has a strict identification procedures to ensure that your child is protected. All of our teachers are certified in first aid and child CPR. When outside the classroom, on the playground or on a field trip, teachers carry cell phones and first aid kits. Of course, prevention is key so our classrooms and playgrounds are designed to be safe for your youngster to run and play.

Since 2004: The philosophies embraced by The Kangaroo Club were created by a working mom searching for a quality program for her own two children. Our center has been privately owned and operated by that same woman for 5 years.

name: The Village School & Child Care Center L.C.
The Winston School Afterschool Program
detail:
The Winston School is a small college preparatory school designed to maximize the potential of bright students who learn differently.® Through individualized learning strategies, our students are empowered to meet confidently the challenges of tomorrow.

The philosophy of The Winston School is truly reflected in the School’s mission statement. The environment and curriculum of The Winston School are designed for bright students who learn differently®. Learning disabilities are unique to the individual and may be manifested in various academic areas; each person deserves the opportunity to learn in the manner appropriate for their own distinctive style. Through Winston’s Testing and Evaluation Center, students are assessed and teachers are provided with the learning profiles, training, and resources needed to respond to the needs of the students. As cornerstones of the philosophy, the Winston community believes

-  Learning requires self-discipline
-  Learning requires the active participation and support of the student and family
-  Learning focuses on long-term goals
-  Learning is enhanced by understanding one’s particular strengths and weaknesses in the learning process
-  Learning requires the continual development of technical skills needed for reading, writing, and mathematics
- Learning is the process of continual elaboration on the student’s knowledge base
- Learning requires courage and tenacity
- Learning strengthens self-esteem

name: The Yellow School
detail:
Founded in 1974, the Yellow School is part of MDPC Children’s Ministries. Recognizing that the early years of a child’s life are the most important for laying foundations of faith and for social, emotional and cognitive development, the school provides each child with acceptance, respect and love in a Christian environment. It is a place in which children learn about their uniqueness as children of God and develop new relationships. The school provides an environment in which each child is free to explore, experiment, discover, make decisions and problem solve. We encourage curiosity and independence.

We believe the love of God binds us together. In that love we welcome and respect children of all faiths and we provide a welcoming and loving community in which the children work and play together and learn of God’s love for us all.

The Yellow School curricula are developed using guidelines set forth by the Texas Education Agency (TEA) and the findings of the latest brain research. Curricula is written to address the needs of each individual and the class as a whole. Learning activities appropriate to the developmental levels of the children are designed to teach reading and language arts, mathematics, science, social studies, art, music, Spanish, and the development of fine and gross motor skills, as well as faith development. Kindergarten children attend a computer class weekly.

name: Thompson Elementary YMCA ASP
detail:
With so many demands on today's families, parents need all the support they can get. That's why child care at the Y is about more than looking after kids. It's about nurturing their development by providing a safe place to learn foundational skills, develop healthy, trusting relationships and build self-reliance through the Y values of caring, honesty, respect, responsibility and faith. We partner with you, reinforcing the values you teach at home.

At the YMCA of Greater Houston, we offer the options you may be looking for in our after school programs. With locations throughout the greater Houston community, our programs have a long history of helping children grow in spirit, mind and body.

We offer child care to infants 6 weeks to 12 years old, after-school care and summer camp care, all while providing your child with love, attention and academically focused activities in a fun and safe environment.

Our parents have the upmost confidence that their child is being cared for each day in a loving and respectful environment. We understand that choosing child care for your little one is an important decision, so that’s why we pride ourselves on our warm and loving caretakers. Please come by our nurture center for a visit and see why Through A Child’s Eyes is your child’s home away from home or simply call for more information.

detail: Founded by Annie and Willie Nelson in 1995, and originally located on the Nelson's property in Spicewood, Texas, Tierra Vista Montessori moved to Marble Falls in 2007 to service the growing demand for quality education in the Highland Lakes area.

name: Tiger's Den Martial Arts & Fitness Clear Lake, LLC
detail:
Enroll your child in an enriching, fun after school program - without the stress of providing transportation! We will pick up your child up at school, and then bring him or her straight to our dojo for an afternoon full of martial arts, fun and games, exercise, homework and lessons on life.

Your children will learn firsthand the importance of focus, attentiveness, commitment and discipline - and they will have a great time while they are learning. Whether you need to enroll your kids in a program to keep them safe while you work, or you just want a program that will enrich your child's life now and in the future - Tiger's Den is the place to be.

Our supervised, structured program teaches your children important qualities, such as confidence, self-esteem, pride and self-respect in a manner that is fun for them and worry-free for you.

Most importantly, we believe that children need to have fun! At Time for Kids Daycare, we often have exciting activities planned, play lots of games, and read to the children everyday. Children learn best from experiencing the world around them.

name: Toys Day Care
detail: As a parent, you want the best for your child. You want them to be happy, to have friends and valuable experiences. At every age, want to them to grow and to be the very best person they can be. Unfortunately, because of life's demands, you can't be with your child as much as you'd like. But you can enjoy your peace of mind of knowing that your child is happy and secure at Toys Day Care Center. At Toys Day Care, we do everything possible to make your child feel loved and respected. He or she will make friends, learn new skills, hear stories, and learn a variety of interesting things. The curriculum at Toys Day Care Center is bilingual, encourages friendship, cooperation, and multi-cultural acceptance, and promotes confidence. Toys Day Care has given parents a nurturing place for their children for three years at this location. Conveniently located on Piedras between northeast and central El Paso, it's just minutes from Fort Bliss. Toys Day Care offers competitive weekly rates. Hourly and by-the -day rates are available to parents who need to drop off a child for just a few hours or for the day. Children are not admitted when they are ill to prevent infecting others. This offers a healthier environment, and allows sick children to get well in the care of a loved one who can better tend to their medical and personal needs.

detail:
It is indeed an honor to welcome you. This website gives us a great opportunity to gather, learn and share quality information that will positively affect ourselves and our Head Start children and families.

name: Treasure Cove
detail:
The Fellowship at Cinco Ranch is excited to serve the surrounding community through its Weekday Preschool Program. Investing in the lives of children is one of the most rewarding and important callings of life. To make God known and to share the love of Jesus with little ones while stimulating intellectual development is an awesome privilege.
Preschoolers will learn how to build relationships with others in a Christ-centered environment with the help of loving teachers who will guide them in music, play, creative arts, group time, outdoor recreation, lunch and rest time. Our goal is to make each child feel special and loved as they enjoy new experiences and opportunities to learn.Treasure Cove serves children ages 1-5.
    All classes are from 9:00 am to 2:00 pm
    We offer two, three and five day programs depending on the age of the child
    Treasure Cove uses the WEE Learn Curriculum published by Lifeway Press as a resource and the Frog Street Phonics Program in our preschool program.

name: Tree House Incorporated
detail:
At the Tree House, the health and happiness of your children are our primary business. 

What we offer...
-We offer care for children ages 6 weeks to 12 years
-Balanced and nutritious meals as part of our Federal Food Program which include breakfast, lunch, snack,
-A new 3000 sq foot gymnasium with a projection screen, where kids can do everything from yoga to zumba, as well as playing inside on rainy days
-3 large playgrounds geared towards each age group
-An aftershool program with homework assistance for our school age kids
-Devoted staff; all of which are CPR & First Aid certified; and are required to complete 24 hours of child development training yearly
-A secuirty/survelance system with cameras in each classroom and throughout the daycare and playgrounds
-Classrooms that are always at or below state required ratios
-Summer program for school age kids with weekly field trips and fun activities
-Workforce solutions CCS Vendor

name: Tri-County Head Start
detail: Head Start is a comprehensive program that serves children ages 3-5 and their families. It is a child focused program with the overall goal of increasing the school readiness of young children in low income families.

name: Trinity By The Sea Day School
detail:
Trinity Day School is an outreach ministry of Trinity by the Sea Episcopal Church.
We care for children ages 15 months to through 5 years.
We provide excellence in child care for toddlers and preschool children in a loving Christian environment.  Our program includes music, art, math, science, language, fine and gross motor activities, social and emotional activities, and cognitive activities. We also offer a morning Pre-Kindergarten program which surpasses State guidelines. 
Full or part-time schedules available.

name: Trinity Child Development Center
detail: For over ten years, Trinity Child Development Center has been committed to providing a loving Christian environment while building a strong spiritual, academic, and social foundation for young children.  We are licensed by the Texas Department of Protective and Regulatory Services.

name: Trinity Extended Day
detail:
The Trinity School of Texas believes that each student is a manifestation of the Creator God, a unique individual in a social matrix searching for self-expression and identity. The school endeavors to provide a developmentally appropriate intellectual challenge in an environment and an atmosphere of understanding, guidance, and love so that all students may achieve their full academic and personal potential. The school as a family encourages each student to develop the life skills of independence
and interdependence.

Beginning with the foundation of an Early Childhood program, the curriculum strives to offer a harmony among academic subjects, visual and performing arts, and physical education, culminating in the college preparatory program of the Upper School. Students are consistently encouraged and guided to develop personal initiative, independence of mind, clear and accurate expression of thought, and respect for their own health and well-being. The curriculum and regular religious observances seek to demonstrate to students the love of God, the stewardship for his creation, and the responsibility to love and care for others even as they are loved. Education at The Trinity School of Texas endeavors not only to enhance what students know, but also to affect who they are and how they relate to others.

The philosophy and purpose of The Trinity School of Texas are exhibited in our students not only when they are at school but also as they enter into the larger world, well prepared to function independently and with charity in the pursuit of knowledge, with a proper regard for themselves as children of God, and with a love of and responsibility for God’s creation. We hope to have engendered in each student an enthusiasm for life-long learning, a respect and regard for others, and a commitment to find solutions to personal, societal, and global problems.

name: Trinity Lutheran Center for Children
detail:
Trinity Lutheran Child Care has been caring for Brownsville's children since 1985. We believe that all children are special and we offer a quality child care program for infants, toddlers, preschoolers and after-school students. Our goal is to provide a safe, comfortable, Christian environment for early learning and development. Our curriculum encourages social, emotional, physical, intellectual and spiritual growth. We strive to help each child learn self-discipline and independence, as well as, learn to relate to others, value friendship, and to respect one another. 

We encourage parents to come to our facility with their child/children for an informal tour. We look forward to visiting with you and meeting your family's child care needs.

name: Trinity Lutheran Child Development Center
detail: Trinity Lutheran Early Childhood Ministry is a Christ centered School where we are grounded in the Word of God and dedicated to showing the love of Jesus to all our students and their families. Trinity is much more than a daycare center. We have the rare opportunity, with Jesus as our foundation, to provide care not only to our students but to the entire family. Through our Jesus Time curriculum we offer a take home sheet that allows families to study God’s Word together at home. We also have special events to bring families together in God’s Name to celebrate His love in our lives. We believe that God has called you to this place at this time and it is our privilege to respond to that call by showing your family His grace and love!

name: Trinity Lutheran Childrens Ctr
detail: Our goal at Trinity is to provide families of the community, church, and school with a safe, educational, Christ–centered Early Childhood experience. We strive to work in partnership with parents who have the primary and most critical role in the nurturing of their child. It is also our intent to help parents strengthen the family unit according to God’s plan and purpose.  Our caring and well-trained staff members serve as positive role models and provide care that is supportive, nurturing,and responsive to each child’s individual needs. All staff meet and exceed the TDFPS training standards and are certified in CPR and First Aid. Several of our staff members are Certified Teachers.
business hours: Monday through Friday, from 6:30 a.m. to 6:00 p.m.

name: Trinity Lutheran Preschool
detail: Trinity Lutheran Preschool is committed to Christian education.  Our Christian preschool is an extension of the mission and ministry of Trinity Lutheran Church.  Through the school, we reach the younger children of our community, teaching them in a spiritual environment.  We teach them how to use the Bible, God’s Word for development of their faith, for a guide in life, and as a primary evangelism tool.

name: Trinity Lutheran Preschool
detail:
Our school has been in operation for 16 years and continues through God's Grace to surround children with the love of Jesus every day!
Children ages 18 months up to PreKindergarten enjoy developmentally appropriate learning activities as well as supervised outdoor play and
center time.
We offer QUALITY CARE IN A CHRISTIAN ENVIRONMENT!

name: Trinity Lutheran School Extended Care
detail: Trinity provides supervised care for children before and after regular school hours. Extended care is available from 7:00 AM through 6:00 PM. Students arriving before 7:30 AM must report to Room 101. At 7:30 AM students in grades 1-8 will be sent to the designated before school care classroom. At 3:30 PM all students not picked up must report to the appropriate extended care room, or they must be under the direct supervision of a parent, teacher or coach.

name: Triple L Ranch Child Development Center
detail:
At Triple L Ranch our focus is on providing Love, Laughter and Learning throughout the day.
The three L's provide us with the base for what we stand for:
Love: We want each child to feel LOVED in their parents’ absence.
Laughter: It is important to LAUGH and have Fun during the day
Learn: We want to provide each child with the necessary tools to LEARN     Knowing the tremendous impact the early years have on a child, it is our goal to provide a supportive environment. We work together with parents to make each child’s years with us a positive and beneficial experience. We believe that it is our job as Caregivers and Parents to ensure each child is ready for the challenges ahead of them.

name: Troy Headstart
detail: Head Start is a comprehensive child development program for low-income families designed to meet the needs of children age 3 to 5 including children with disabilities.  Components emphasized are education, health (medical, dental, nutrition, and mental health), and social services.  Parent involvement is an essential part of the program.  Head Start represents an organized method of assisting families to assess their needs.  Special needs children receive a full range of Head Start developmental services.
business hours: Monday thru Friday: 8:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

name: Truman Price Elementary
detail: I think you might agree with me that reading is extremely important.  Students who read are more successful in all the academic content areas. So please ensure that your child reads at least 20 minutes everyday.  Make sure that your child knows that you value reading and let your children catch you reading.  Find opportunities to read with your child such as road signs while you are driving,  magazines while waiting in a doctor's lobby, or just reading for leisure.  Another thing that you can do to help children become better readers is to use close-caption when they are watching television.  Let's keep our students reading!

name: TSTC Early Head Start Child Development
Tucker Headstart CDC
detail:
More than 40 years ago, we set out to provide a basic necessity for many Texas families... quality child care. Today, Child Care Associates is the largest private non-profit child development organization in this area, operating 37 child development centers throughout Fort Worth and Tarrant County. We also oversee several other programs and special initiatives in this region, all focused on early childhood development.

Child Care Associates currently has a collaboration with two Tarrant County school districts using resources provided by Fort Worth ISD and Hurst/Euless/Bedford ISD that consists of 40 classrooms on a number of elementary school campuses. We also have other local collaborations where ISD teachers spend quality classroom time in our child development centers.

name: Walnut Creek Elementary-YMCA NW
detail:
After a long academic day, kids want to have fun! At the YMCA, we provide a balanced program of choices and structured activities. Research shows that kids do better in school when they are engaged in enriching activities during after school hours. We provide an educational environment with a unique mix of activities that focus on the assets necessary for positive development, while keeping the afternoon fun!

NEW! Y-Fit Program: Y-Fit provides students with 60 minutes of structured physical activity and nutrition education programming. Y-Fit utilizes SPARK, a research-based physical education and coordinated school health program designed to increase physical activity and promote physical activity beyond classes to become a component of an active lifestyle. Students will participate daily in activities such as Fitness Fun, Cool Cooperatives, Great Games & Super Sports. In addition, students will experience hands on nutrition education with recipe planning, food demonstrations & more.

name: Waltrip Child Development Lab

We are dedicated to the education and care of infants, toddlers and preschoolers. With a foundation built upon a strong and uniquely progressive educational philosophy. Waltrip CDC upholds an image of the child as a powerful, competent, capable and integral member of the community.

name: Warren Montessori School
detail:
Warren Montessori School opened on January 05, 2004 with 75 students,which has grown up to 220 students. We are also currently in the process of obtaining accreditation from AMS. Our staff is AMS, AMI and MACTE certified teachers.

Our classrooms are big and spacious. The covered playground and indoor gymnasium give children the freedom to run around and exercise even during inclement weather days.

Parent's involvement in school events is always welcomed. We have parent's education nights, hold multicultural events and celebrate various festivals.

name: Water Oak School
detail:
Water Oak Preschool was founded in 1980 by Stan and Connie Shipp.  Our commitment in providing children a safe and secure environment where our students can grow and develop a strong academic and spiritual foundation has continued over the past 32 years. In August of 2012, Kevin and Kristin Monk were given the opportunity to purchase the preschool.  They had experienced, firsthand, through their three children, what a school such as Water Oak can do.  The foundation laid in education, social, and emotional development and Christian values is far-reaching.

    Water Oak is blessed to have a degreed and experienced teaching staff consisting of Mrs. Fred (Jody Horton), Mrs. Joy (Joy Lane), Mrs. Gail (Gail Hicks), and Ms. Tiffani (Tiffani Contreras).  Our teachers are assisted and supported by Mrs. Fred who also serves as Water Oak's Director.  Each day we are blessed to serve our families and children on this exciting start to their educational journey!

Monday through F
riday, from 7:30 A.M. until 5:30

Wee Care at Sha's World Child Care
Wee Learn Center
detail: As an outreach of First Baptist Church of Longview, Texas, The Wee Learn Center was developed to help children grow spiritually, emotionally, intellectually, socially and physically. What they learn during their first years will shpare their attitudes about themselves and everyone around them. We beleive faith and education go hand and hand to glorify God although our school is open to any child regardless of race or religious belief.

name: Wee Wisdom
detail:
Wee Wisdom Daycare & Academic Center in El Paso, Texas promotes a positive attitude toward learning in the first years of school.​ Established in 1976. 

“Accept me as I am, so I may learn what I can become” is the aspiration of this school.​

The goal of Wee Wisdom is to have its students acquire the important academic fundamentals and develop, through success, a sense of personal worth and the ability to achieve their total potential. Being private allows Wee Wisdom the flexibility of staying with old educational philosophies that work and adding new programs that enhance those philosophies. Wee Wisdom’s courses engage the student to think more effectively in developing effective cognitive and linguistic skills. Thus they can integrate these skills to achieve making the transition from knowing what to do to actually doing what they know should be done.

detail:
The Wesleyan Academe Mission is to provide academic excellence in a multicultural Christian environment which prepares, nurtures, and challenges students to discover themselves as independent critical thinkers and thriving members of the community.

The Wesleyan Academe offers a traditional school setting as an alternative to daycare / childcare for the younger child in options of a half or full day. We also offer before or after daycare / childcare for ages 2 years to First Grade students.

A child's capacity for learning and quest for knowledge is never greater than during their early years. We seek to nurture the inquisitive mind by opening avenues of exploration and intellectual adventure.  We gladly accept the opportunity to help each student to grow in spirit, in academic capability, in social grace and in an understanding of the human condition that will enhance his future endeavors in and out of the classroom.

detail: West Austin Youth Academy builds its program on the premise that each child is a unique individual with a definite growth and developmental pattern. In addition, we are committed to the belief that early childhood education is vitally important to our children's future.

name: West Elementary - YMCA
detail:
After a long academic day, kids want to have fun! At the YMCA, we provide a balanced program of choices and structured activities. Research shows that kids do better in school when they are engaged in enriching activities during after school hours. We provide an educational environment with a unique mix of activities that focus on the assets necessary for positive development, while keeping the afternoon fun!

NEW! Y-Fit Program: Y-Fit provides students with 60 minutes of structured physical activity and nutrition education programming. Y-Fit utilizes SPARK, a research-based physical education and coordinated school health program designed to increase physical activity and promote physical activity beyond classes to become a component of an active lifestyle. Students will participate daily in activities such as Fitness Fun, Cool Cooperatives, Great Games & Super Sports. In addition, students will experience hands on nutrition education with recipe planning, food demonstrations & more.

name: White Settlement Head Start and Child Development Center
detail:
More than 40 years ago, we set out to provide a basic necessity for many Texas families... quality child care. Today, Child Care Associates is the largest private non-profit child development organization in this area, operating 37 child development centers throughout Fort Worth and Tarrant County. We also oversee several other programs and special initiatives in this region, all focused on early childhood development.

Child Care Associates currently has a collaboration with two Tarrant County school districts using resources provided by Fort Worth ISD and Hurst/Euless/Bedford ISD that consists of 40 classrooms on a number of elementary school campuses. We also have other local collaborations where ISD teachers spend quality classroom time in our child development centers.

detail:
Whether a newborn or pre-teen, your child will love WonderWorld! And you will appreciate the wonderful felling of peace of mind you get from knowing that your child is learning, growing, and experiencing a WonderWorld's safe, caring, and stimulating environment.

The facility at 12340 Paseo Nuevo has a 5,000 square foot building with many classrooms to accommodate various age groups, a commercial kitchen that offers nutricious meals and snacks, and a library of age appropriate books. The playground offers children plenty of fresh air, outdoor playtime, and a place for physical fitness classes for older children.

WonderWorld is as concerned about your child's safety and well-being as you are. All employees are professional caregivers for children and have submitted to a police background check before hiring. detail:
Woodcrest MDO and Preschool uses the Carpenter's Kids curriculum, "the blueprints for building God's Kingdom one child at a time." This curriculum encompasses many early childhood objectives such as letter and phonemic recognition, shapes and colors of the month, numbers, calendar skills, social skills, imaginative play, learning about nature and much, much more.

In addition, as we introduce letters of the alphabet, the curriculum includes a Bible story that also begins with that letter. Children learn through these stories and throughout the year about God's word and how He wants us to live. Students are encouraged to pray and to practice good moral values with one another such as sharing and kindness on a daily basis. Our overall theme and slogan at Woodcrest is "Let your light shine." We let our light shine for Jesus every day by being kind to others.

name: YMCA PTA Care Greathouse
detail:
The Midland YMCA began in 1953 with 1162 charter members. A temporary board with George H.W. Bush as Chairman set out to raise the funds needed to start the organization. In September 1953, the first elected Board was installed with Curt Inman serving as chairman. These Midlanders were committed to providing adequate recreational and social facilities for the families who had been brought here to work in various phases of the oil industry. Programs began with a bicycle club for boys and girls and a men's volleyball class that met in the school gym. The YMCA of Midland is an association of people of all ages, ethnic groups and religious affiliations united with a mission to put Christian principles into practice through programs that build healthy spirit, mind and body for all. Major program services include after school child care, summer day camps, teen Youth & Government, aquatic programs, youth sports, adult sports, parent-child programs, Y-Indian Guides and Y-Indian Princesses, and adult and senior health and fitness programs. YMCA programs teach youth and families important values such as honesty, responsibility and respect. Through a variety of fun and rewarding activities, youth also develop valuable skills while they gain confidence and self-esteem.
The YMCA's experience lies in building "strong kids, strong families and strong communities." We have more...come see!

name: YMCA-Jollyville Elementary
detail:
The YMCA of Austin offers afterschool care for children in grades K - 5 at fifteen licensed sites in three Austin area school districts. The Afterschool Care Program provides on-site care for your child, beginning when school is dismissed and continuing until 6:30 p.m.

Participating children learn valuable social and scholastic skills in a safe, fun, and supervised environment.

The afterschool care program offers a constructive balance of counselor led activities and free time for child exploration. Daily theme activities include arts and crafts, science/math activities, nutrition/wellness activities, presentation activities (music, theater, cooking, etc) and literacy. In addition, the Y delivers CATCH physical activity lessons daily and has made a commitment to meet the Y's Healthy Eating and Physical Activity Standards (HEPA). Lastly, there is always time for homework, a nutritious afternoon snack, and outside time on the playground.

name: Young Scholars Academy
detail:
Young Scholars Academy is a child care center serving the San Angelo, TX area since 2003. Our mission is to promote growth and development in each of our attending children. If you are looking for a quality after school program to enroll your child in, we offer child care up to age 12! Our experienced staff is knowledgeable and experienced as well as CPR/First Aid certified. We are open from 6:30 am - 6:00 pm Monday through Friday. For more information on our day care center, please call today!

Maybe you have been searching for a day care center for your child for a long time. Look no further than Young Scholars Academy for all of your child care needs. There are several key components you should look for when you are searching for day care centers, one of the most important components being the staff. The American Academy of Pedaitrics recommends a ratio of one staff member for 3 to 5 small children and one staff member for 7 to 10 older children. At Young Scholars Academy, we have an adequate amount of staff members to ensure that your child's needs are met.

Another aspect that makes our day care center stand out from the rest has to do with our meals! We provide all of our children with nutritious meals including breakfast, lunch and a delicious afternoon snack. If your child requires a special diet, we provide us with a note from your physician with alternative foods we may serve your child.

name: Young World Kindergarten and Day Care Center
detail: Young World Kindergarten & Day Care is a state licensed child care facility providing professional early instruction to children in Temple, TX. Director Vicki Wadsworth and her experienced and qualified staff will make sure your children receive proper instruction and care.

name: Your Growing Child
detail: Inspired by a passion for education & a love of children, YGC has a strong sense of community and wants to partner with our local families to help kids to grow and learn. YGC promotes a fun-filled, nurturing and educational environment for all of our children to bloom into responsible, considerate and contributing young people. Through our low teacher-child ratios and highly exceptional teachers, the children have the opportunity to grow emotionally, socially and intellectually by interacting, exploring and learning with others in a positive, safe and healthy environment. As a family owned and operated organization, Christy Vickrey welcomes positive family involvement. We respect our parents as the primary providers of love, care and education to their children, but we encourage a parent-teacher approach where the needs of every child comes first in order to experience the benefits of excellent early childhood education and school-age programs. YGC supports families by creating a quality childcare program led by inspiring and loving teachers who nurture children as they learn, play and grow. Classes are available for children as young as eight weeks through age 5. We also offer before and after school care for school-age children as well as Summer Camp. Stop by today for more information and a tour of our center.
