Welcome to Zion Lutheran School! Thank you for your interest in Zion Lutheran School.  It is of utmost importance for children to have a good foundation in their Christian faith as well as solid academic training.  I’m very glad that you see this need and desire to give your child the best possible Christian foundation as well as the best possible education.

Zion Lutheran School holds both national and state accreditation.  Our certified teachers are gifted individuals who have a genuine concern for each of their students.  Our students consistently score high on the Iowa Test of Basic Skills (ITBS) and participate in a wide range of extra-curricular activities.

When your child is part of Zion Lutheran School, they are part of so much more.  They are part of a caring family where they will learn and grow both academically and in their faith walk with Christ.  At Zion Lutheran School, we recognize that each child is unique and has gifts and interests that will enhance our school family.

As a parent, your child’s best interest is foremost in your mind.  And choosing the right school to provide the basis for their Christian and academic lives is vitally important.  I hope that you will choose to partner with us at Zion Lutheran School to provide a Christ-centered educational experience for your child.

detail: Denim and Diamonds Pre-School Kid’s Klub is a newly formed institution located in the heart of New Waverly, Texas.   This is a family owned establishment. She felt that the community could benefit from the skills, education and experience that she has developed throughout the 40 years she has spent in the Child Care Industry.  Mrs. Aubrey graduated from Texas Southern University with a Bachelors Degree in Home Economics Education with an emphasis in Child Development, Early Childhood and Special Needs Children. name: Decatur Child Development Center
detail: The mission of Texas Neighborhood Services is found in its chartered by-laws originally created in 1965 and modified throughout the corporation’s history. The chartered mission is to administer the social programs of the United States, State, Public or Private assignment or award in the various counties applied for and to administer other programs designed to assist citizens in the counties we serve. Texas Neighborhood Services strategically targets this mission with the support of three significant groups in the community; representatives of the low-income, elected officials from the public sector, and business leaders from the private sector. The objective of working with these groups is to seek out, identify, and aid in the elimination of the causes of poverty within the communities served, help people prepare for, find and retain long term employment, and match employers with a quality, job-ready workforce. TNS executes this mission to make the entire community more responsive to the needs and interests of its citizens. This is accomplished by mobilizing available resources and bringing about a greater institutional sensitivity to the individuals being helped while at the same time developing a system of priorities among projects, activities, and areas, as needed, for the most effective and efficient use of resources.

name: David Sublasky Head Start / Early Head Start

detail:
Welcome! To the place your child can play, learn and develop. To a supportive and secure environment. To a professional child care setting in which you can be confident. Welcome to Play and Learn.

Our philosophy is simple. We believe that giving children the ability to interact in a small-group learning environment provides the best opportunity to help them develop their own unique concepts and ideas. We believe that the best way to help children expand their cognitive, social, emotional, language and motor abilities is by giving them challenging, stress-free activities in a nurturing environment. We believe that for young children, play is the path children take to learning, and helps them develop a meaningful understanding of the world around them.

The ability to connect with others is a critical asset in life, and because we live in an increasingly global world, children who learn to speak foreign languages will be better prepared to communicate with others—at home and abroad.

At Crossing Borders Preschool, we help children prepare for the future at the age when they are most eager to learn. We are not just a language school; our offerings go far beyond simply teaching children how to speak Spanish, Chinese, and French. We offer quality education options for children, with comprehensive language immersion programs that are effective and, equally important, fun!

name: Camacho Childcare Inc. Teddy Bear Academy
detail:
Teddy Bear Academy is ....
YOUR daycare!  Every family takes part is making this daycare special! 

Teddy Bear Academy is family owned and operated. Now, what on earth does that mean for you?? Simply put, this means that we are here for YOU!!  Yes, YOU.  The one seating down looking for a new or better daycare to place your child. 

A few years back, I was doing the same thing.  I was a stay at home mother to my first child, but finances wouldn’t let me be the same for our second.  We began scouting out different daycares and nurseries and we came across a common complaint…”just doesn’t feel right”.  Dirty facilities or teachers that were indifferent to my concerns, directors that would only spout out rules and regulations…. I wanted that warm feeling when I drop off my kiddo and baby; like leaving them with family or friends.  But I didn’t find it, so I MADE it. 

Teddy Bear’s Owner and Director are the same and on site all the time, no middle man here, plus the real boss running the show is YOU.  I welcome feedback and requests from my families all the time, and strive to be everything that you want us to be!  Children deserve the best care, and parents deserve a warm welcome and a say in what happens at daycare, and you will get that and hopefully a little more here at Teddy Bear Academy!

name: Burleson Child Development Center Inc
detail:
We believe all children have a natural desire to play, to explore, to learn and to express themselves as individuals. As children engage in their environment, they strive to understand the world and all its properties and mysteries. As they grow, children develop relationships with peers and adults and learn to communicate to express themselves and their ideas. Their engagement in their environment and relationships with others are experiences that help children build on their understanding of the world and their place in it. At Burleson Child Development Center, Inc., we want children to express themselves freely, to think critically, to work collaboratively and to live and explore actively.

The cornerstone of Burleson Child Development Center, Inc. program is a conviction that each child is unique, highly capable, and has a right to be valued and respected for who she or he is. We believe that high self-esteem is an important goal for children, and this belief underlies all decisions, systems, policies, and planning, and generates a feeling of respect by and for each individual. We believe that healthy, respectful relationships are the most significant factor in developing self esteem; therefore, we emphasize the importance of communication skills in our staff training.

name: Baldwin Crew
detail:
Ross F. Baldwin Elementary School opened on August 23, 2010. The school is located at 12200 Meridian Park Blvd in the Meridian neighborhood in southwest Austin. Our colors are purple and gold and our mascot is the bobcat.

Our school is named after Ross F. Baldwin, respected community leader and dedicated student mentor. Mr. Baldwin was born on December 11, 1924 in Wortham, Texas, where he was the youngest of four siblings. He was a veteran of World War II in the Seabees 4th Special Battalion, serving in the Pacific. He founded Baldwin Beauty Schools in 1979 and served as President for more than 25 years. He was also an active Rotary member from 1982 until his death in 2007. He served as president of the Rotary Club of Austin-Oak Hill and was honored with awards including Rotarian of the Year and Rotary Hall of Fame.

Mr. Baldwin was active in the community through service and business organizations, the public schools, public affairs and nonprofit organizations. He was well known for his dedication to mentoring Austin area students. A mentor at Joslin Elementary School for nearly 30 years, he mentored several students each year, and supported their success by attending games, plays, scout meetings, and other activities. In 2005, he was named Mentor of the Year by AISD’s Partners in Education. He set an example by involving the students he mentored in the Rotary Club by having them volunteer their time in various Rotary activities.

Baldwin Elementary also has a school song written by our music teacher, Susan Stevens. It embodies the spirit of our close community.

detail:

Our children benefit from receiving a strong foundation in academics, and the development of social/emotional and motor skills. In addition, the families have the opportunity to participate in their child’s learning through the weekly family activity packets, monthly parent meetings, and volunteer opportunities.

Oxford Head Start families have access to adult education classes, such as GED, ESL, Computer, Parenting Education, Fatherhood and Healthy Relationship. To meet the special needs of a child or the family, our health, nutrition, intervention and social services collaborate to provide guidance and resources. Research shows that children have more success in school and life when they have the support of caring adults and good role models.

At Oxford Head Start, every day has the potential to be “great” because each child has “great” potential.

This program offers classes for English as a Second Language (ESL), General Education Certification (GED) and Computer (Spanish). It also assists graduating adults enroll in college courses and exam preparation.

The Head Start and Early Head Start programs provide a full day program for non-working parents, and an extended day program for working parents. This includes breakfast, lunch and a snack daily for each student, and a comprehensive accredited curriculum. Our teaching staff hold either a bachelor's, associate's and/or a child development associate's in addition to many years of early childhood experience. detail: The mission of Texas Neighborhood Services is found in its chartered by-laws originally created in 1965 and modified throughout the corporation’s history. The chartered mission is to administer the social programs of the United States, State, Public or Private assignment or award in the various counties applied for and to administer other programs designed to assist citizens in the counties we serve. Texas Neighborhood Services strategically targets this mission with the support of three significant groups in the community; representatives of the low-income, elected officials from the public sector, and business leaders from the private sector. The objective of working with these groups is to seek out, identify, and aid in the elimination of the causes of poverty within the communities served, help people prepare for, find and retain long term employment, and match employers with a quality, job-ready workforce. TNS executes this mission to make the entire community more responsive to the needs and interests of its citizens. This is accomplished by mobilizing available resources and bringing about a greater institutional sensitivity to the individuals being helped while at the same time developing a system of priorities among projects, activities, and areas, as needed, for the most effective and efficient use of resources.

detail:
Kid’s Place is considered one of the top learning centers for small children, in Corpus Christi, by many professionals as well as industry leaders. In addition to attributing our success to our Lord’s favor, we believe our secret is in our curriculum. Modeled after the Early Learning Academy of PA, Kid’s Place blends a modified Montessori environment with Introduction to Spanish, Introduction to Math, and the Wee Learn Christian curriculums. In addition, we are a Texas School Ready certified program and a certified Baby Sign Center. More information about our learning theories can be found on our curriculum page.

While academics and development rank very high in the Early Childhood field currently in the US, we would like to emphasize that a safe loving and nurturing environment filled with fun, and prayer of course, are truly the most essential ingredients to help children develop a love for school and learning, which will serve as a base for many future years in education. Therefore, while it is important to look at how well our students rank in the primary grades or how well regarded our educational theories are, our emphasis remains on our children having fun and loving school.  Therefore Four favorite friends we have at Kid’s Place are the characters which teach our specials: Healthy Hanna on Mondays, Senora Heather on Tuesdays, Silly Val the Science Gal on Wednesdays and Bible Buddy Betty on Thursdays. The kids sure do like to have fun with them and it is amazing to see how much learning is absorbed when directed fun is taking place.

Our core curriculum takes place Tuesday through Thursday between 9am to 2pm. Our extended hours of enrichment are from 7 to 9am, 2 to 6 pm, and Monday& Friday. These extended hours allow working parents the opportunity to enroll their children in Kid’s Place. Our extended hours are an enhancement to our core curriculum.

We are a year round academy with our school year following the district calendars from August to May, and our “Dive Into Literature” program taking place in the summer. Our calendar mimics the district and our yearly budget, including holidays is divided into 12 months. If parents choose to take off the summer months they are welcome to do so. However, in order to hold their child’s spot they need to pay a reregistration fee prior to leaving for the summer. We do have Christmas & Spring break as well as a small break in the beginning of summer.

detail:
With the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964, President Lyndon Johnson solidified his commitment to forging new opportunities for the poor in the United States by mobilizing financial and human resources to eliminate poverty.  To assist in fighting President Johnson’s “War on Poverty”, local Community Action Agencies (CAA’s) were created to provide a wide range of human services at the community level to help individuals build self-sufficiency and rise out of poverty.

Nueces County Community Action Agency (NCCAA) is a private, non-profit corporation created with the Economic Opportunity Act of 1964, to lead the battle of President Lyndon Johnson’s “War on Poverty”.  Our agency offers a wide variety of programs, such as, Community Services, Weatherization, Utility Assistance, Housing, Information and Referral, Birth-to-Five Head Start and Healthy Marriage.  NCCAA’s Birth-to-Five Head Start Program serves over 1,200 children and their families in Nueces County with education, health, disabilities, mental health, nutrition, and family services.

detail: The mission of Texas Neighborhood Services is found in its chartered by-laws originally created in 1965 and modified throughout the corporation’s history. The chartered mission is to administer the social programs of the United States, State, Public or Private assignment or award in the various counties applied for and to administer other programs designed to assist citizens in the counties we serve. Texas Neighborhood Services strategically targets this mission with the support of three significant groups in the community; representatives of the low-income, elected officials from the public sector, and business leaders from the private sector. The objective of working with these groups is to seek out, identify, and aid in the elimination of the causes of poverty within the communities served, help people prepare for, find and retain long term employment, and match employers with a quality, job-ready workforce. TNS executes this mission to make the entire community more responsive to the needs and interests of its citizens. This is accomplished by mobilizing available resources and bringing about a greater institutional sensitivity to the individuals being helped while at the same time developing a system of priorities among projects, activities, and areas, as needed, for the most effective and efficient use of resources.

name: North Zulch Learning Center
detail:
North Zulch Learning Center in North Zulch, Texas opened its doors in the summer of 2010, serving children aged six weeks to five years, with an after school program for children in grades PK-6th. North Zulch Learning Center is licensed by the state of Texas as a Child Daycare Center with the capacity for 38 children, 6 weeks to 12 years of age. 

Early Head Start Curriculum Goals and Objectives are used as the foundation of their curriculum to provide lessons in the following areas: cognitive, social/emotional, fine/gross motor, and language.  Lessons are based on developmentally appropriate practices through a variety of hands-on activities that teachers implement in their classrooms during small group, large group, centers, and with one-on-one instruction. When implementing these activities the goal is to ensure the children have the best learning experience using planned and purposeful strategies. 

Children need to be exposed to new concepts multiple times and across a variety of concepts in order to solidify their understanding. Teachers at NZLC use a gradual release method by modeling, demonstrating and “thinking aloud” so that the children understand the thoughts behind what they are doing. Then the children practice the skills and concepts with the teacher guiding their practice. This process provides children with multiple opportunities for learning and understanding

A daily schedule and daily routine provide the basic structure for each day. Themes are incorporated into the curriculum to provide the children with opportunities to learn about the world in which they live. Examples of themes that are used or have been used include: The Four Seasons; Our Five senses; Our Families; Transportation; Animals; Insects; Firefighters;

detail: Welcome to the XTREME KIDFIT training facilities. We are dedicated to providing the highest quality after school, summer camp & evening programs to kids and adults. As a member of  XTREME KIDFIT, you and your family will have the opportunity to build and excel as an athlete in the sports of Crossfit, Judo, Jujitsu, Karate, and Triathlon; which includes swimming, running and cycling.  XTREME KIDFIT programs are designed to allow beginners a comfortable place to start and challenge the more experienced athlete. It has been our philosophy that the promotion of health and wellness through physical activity will bring about coordination, confidence, discipline, and awareness, supplying our team members with the tools needed to lead healthy and productive lives.

name: Valeries Kid Kare
detail:
We have been serving the day care needs of Saginaw, TX since 1989 and is family owned and operated by Valerie Tankersley.

We have a preschool program to help children before they start school and provides care for children ages 0-12. Breakfast lunch and snacks are served as well as providing transportation to three of the local schools (Saginaw Elem, Willow Creek Elem and Bryson Elem). Valeries Kid Kare also takes trips to the Saginaw Water Park during the summer months.

We are in 2 separate buildings with our babies and toddler in our original building and our preschool, pre-k and schoolers in a building next door.

We do not offer part-time care. Our rates are weekly, however we can work with you if your pay schedule requires payments be bi-weekly or monthly.

name: Visions of Learning Child Care Center
detail: VISIONS OF LEARNING CHILD CARE CENTER IS DEDICATED TO PROVIDING A WARM, CARING AND LOVING ENVIRONMENT THAT ALLOWS ALL OUR CHILDREN TO DEVELOP AT THEIR OWN PACE.  WE TRULY BELIEVE THAT CHILDREN MUST HAVE A POSITIVE SELF-IMAGE, AND WE PROMOTE THAT! OUR PURPOSE IS TO MAKE READY YOUNG CHILDREN TO ENTER KINDERGARTEN AHEAD OF THE CLASS; KNOWING THE BASIC ESSENTIALS SUCH AS ABC'S, ABLE TO COUNT TO TEN, ABLE TO RECITE THEIR AND THEIR PARENTS' FIRST AND LAST NAMES, AS WELL AS THEIR ADDRESS, AND PHONE NUMBER JUST TO NAME A FEW OF THE THINGS WE TEACH THE CHILDREN.

name: Willow Creek Elementary Northwest YMCA
detail:
After a long academic day, kids want to have fun! At the YMCA, we provide a balanced program of choices and structured activities. Research shows that kids do better in school when they are engaged in enriching activities during after school hours. We provide an educational environment with a unique mix of activities that focus on the assets necessary for positive development, while keeping the afternoon fun!

NEW! Y-Fit Program: Y-Fit provides students with 60 minutes of structured physical activity and nutrition education programming. Y-Fit utilizes SPARK, a research-based physical education and coordinated school health program designed to increase physical activity and promote physical activity beyond classes to become a component of an active lifestyle. Students will participate daily in activities such as Fitness Fun, Cool Cooperatives, Great Games & Super Sports. In addition, students will experience hands on nutrition education with recipe planning, food demonstrations & more.

name: YMCA Afterschool-Lantrip Elementary School
detail:
With so many demands on today's families, parents need all the support they can get. That's why child care at the Y is about more than looking after kids. It's about nurturing their development by providing a safe place to learn foundational skills, develop healthy, trusting relationships and build self-reliance through the Y values of caring, honesty, respect, responsibility and faith. We partner with you, reinforcing the values you teach at home.

At the YMCA of Greater Houston, we offer the options you may be looking for in our after school programs. With locations throughout the greater Houston community, our programs have a long history of helping children grow in spirit, mind and body.

In our hopes that you choose Young Scholars Day School , know that we count it a BIG privilege to be entrusted with your child's early education. Our desire is that what they receive here will impact them through the rest of their school years.

We want for our children to view their school as a continuation of their homes so they can enjoy the time they spend there. We want for you, as the parent, to feel your child is safe and happy in our care.

We believe that value-based education is very important as values are an essential aspect of high character development and a significant part of each person as a whole. That is why we will make sure that positive values are transmitted to the children in as many different ways as possible during our daily routines.

Please, come and visit us. You are always welcome to join our family.

We will create an atmosphere to promote a warm and entertaining hope when they go out into the world. No matter how old they are, they will remember the wonderful times at The Lighthouse Private School and wish they were young again.

Our Mission is to provide an educational, spiritual, and social experience. Each student in the Academy will be encouraged to develop strong academic skills, a feeling of self-worth and responsible behavior, all rooted in the love of God.

detail: The ASYMCA Childcare program offers State licensed, low-cost, high quality before and after school care for elementary school age children throughout the Central Texas Community. The ASYMCA is trained to offer competent, creative, and concerned supervision. Homework time, arts and crafts, games, sports, and story time are just part of the basic program.

detail:
Kidsville’s mission is to provide a safe and creative environment for children after school and benefit the campuses in which we operate.

Kidsville Inc. is owned by Eddie and Kelly Massey, parents of three young children, who understand the need for quality and affordable childcare. Kelly has eleven years of experience with after school programs, such as Kid’s Connection in Bryan ISD and the YMCA in Grapevine-Colleyville ISD. She has also run a home-based after school program serving Birdville ISD school children. Kelly has a B.S. in Rehabilitation Services from the University of North Texas.

Kidsville is committed to giving back to the schools in which it operates by donating a portion of its revenues for school improvements, supplies or programs. Kidsville has donated over $20,000 in the past four years.

name: Head Start Westwood Terrace Elementary
detail:
Family Service Association of San Antonio has been building strong families since 1903. It is the oldest human service agency in San Antonio dedicated to helping children, seniors, and families in need.

From five neighborhood locations and from more than 56 school campuses, Family Service provides high quality service in English and Spanish to the residents of 28 counties of all ethnic and racial backgrounds and all socio-economic levels.

Family Service is a private, non-profit, non-sectarian agency funded by the United Way, United States Department of Health and Human Services, fee-for-service contracts with both public and private organizations, foundation and corporate grants, private contributions, client fees, and outpatient mental health insurance. 

Fees are charged on a sliding scale, and no one is denied help because of their inability to pay the full cost of service.

name: EOAC West Avenue Jump Start
detail:
Head Start and Early Head Start helps to build a foundation for children's success.  Head Start/Early Head Start are comprehensive programs designed to foster the healthy development of young children from low-income families.  The programs have grown from a brief, eight-week summer program for preschoolers in 1965 to a year-round program today, serving children from birth to four and pregnant women.

The Head Start Bureau (HSB), the Administration on Children, Youth and Families (ACYF) Administration for Children and Families (ACF), and the Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) administer the Head Start program.

detail:
The Center for New Communities has launched an early childhood development program that will serve 224 infants, toddlers, expectant mothers and their families in San Antonio (Bexar County) and Fredericksburg (Gillespie County), Texas. With a commitment to the whole family, Center for New Communities and its partnering organizations provides high-quality, developmentally appropriate care and guidance for low-income children and their families that leads to school readiness and strong families.

We believe in cultivating the social, emotional, linguistic, educational, physical and cognitive development of every individual we serve. Our vision is to provide wholistic services so that every child and family have the opportunity to reach their greatest potential.

name: Little Bird Preschool
detail:
Little Bird Preschool began as a home-based preschool and has since expanded into a full time preschool and art studio.

We offer preschool (with full-time child care options), art lessons for children, Parents’ night out, birthday parties, and special art events.

We hope to foster children’s natural sense of wonder about the world and cultivate their curiosity for learning. We provide children with meaningful experiences for play and exploration while nourishing their potential as individuals. Our environment is carefully set up so that children may be in charge of their own learning.

Little Bird Preschool values each child as an individual. We are heavily influenced by the philosophy of Reggio Emilia and play based learning. We wish to engage the mind of the young child through providing an attractive, child focused, creative, art focused and welcoming environment.

We believe that play is essential in the lives of young children and believe that we provide a unique experience to Amarillo, Texas

name: Blossoms Early Childhood Education
detail:
At Blossoms we offer a friendly, educational and nurturing environment for infants, preschool, pre-K and kindergarten kids in the Pleasanton and surrounding areas.

Blossoms has two locations that we affectionately refer to as  "Little Blossoms" enrolling children from 12 months to early 3 years, and "Big Blossoms" enrolling children from 3 years to kindergarten.

Every Blossoms teacher has an individualized, age appropriate, curriculum created specifically for the children in their classrooms.  Our mornings are spent in a classroom learning environment, and our afternoons are filled with music, art, crafts and outdoor activities. 

Blossoms encourages early learning and the development of social skills through play, creative activities and other noncompetitive exercises. As professional educators, our teachers emphasize the growth of the child as a whole.

detail:
At Dulcinea Spanish Learning Center our bilingual education program helps build a foundation for the lifelong process of learning. Your child will experience a thorough early childhood learning program in a bi-cultural environment. We welcome all students, whether they are just beginning their journey into the Spanish language or they are looking to expand their Spanish exposure. Children can learn a second language in the same way they learned their native language, with continuous exposure it comes quite naturally! The benefits of knowing Spanish are quite obvious here in central Texas, however, a second language also adds additional cognitive benefits. Some of which include enhanced problem solving skills, spatial relation skills and heightened creativity. 

Children are immersed from the first day in a loving, 
nurturing and stimulating environment!

No contract required and no strings attached. We are so sure that once you experience to Dulcinea Spanish Learning Center,difference, you and your children will be extremely glad you did.

name: Ms Twanas Kiddie Garden
detail:
Ms.Twana's Kiddie Garden strives to provide working families with a caring, day-and-night care program for their children. Our Kiddie Garden is highly dedicated to early-school development for toddlers and little kids to prepare them for tomorrow's little future.

Ms. Twana's Kiddie Garden incorporates fun and interactive activities into educational exercises that help children build and work on their self-confidence and personal character.  We focus on creating a partnership with parents and/or teachers to ensure that your child or children receives overall support, care and guidance. We make it mandatory to meet with the parents and discuss ways to make their child’s early development not only fun but educational.  

Our Kiddie Garden also focuses on the importance of maintaining and practicing good health for young children. We have a healthy meal plan that does not include pork. We practice good physical health through outside activities and kid-friendly exercises. We take pride in providing a day care facility that tends to your children’s mental health. We have a NO-BULLYING atmosphere. Our Kiddie Garden focuses on learning how to work together by building ourselves and others.

Our Kiddie Garden has extended hours every day of the week so we are always available for the working family of today. Looking for an early morning or late night day care provider because you have to go to work early or want to enjoy a night out with your spouse? We open our day care early in the morning and close late at night.

We pride ourselves on tending to the early school development of your children but the working and personal needs of the parents. We are Twana’s Kiddie Garden.

detail:
A-1 Montessori School, you will discover a warm, welcoming community. Our school environment and curriculum provide children ages 6 weeks to 6 years with a life-long love of learning. Our Montessori teachers are certified in using Dr.Montessori's methods and materials to lovingly guide each child in developing unique abilities within a carefully planned curriculum. Our goal is to provide the learning experiences that allow children to develop the skills to become successful learners wiithin the classroom, and more importantly, to develop self-confidence, independence, compassion, and the sense of responsibility to become successful members of society long after their time at A1 Montessori School is over.

As an authentic Montessori school, our curriculum and programs are designed to build a strong foundation in academics, as well as social, emotional, physical and moral development. This approach encourages a child's independence, self-motivation, and decision-making skills.

Our Montessori teachers recieve continuing ed ucation and participate in ongoing training throughout the year. Supplemental teachers specialize in dance, music, foreign languages, and art. We maintain teacher to student ratios as required by the state of Texas.

Our classrooms are designed to stimulate the child's natural curiosity to explore the world around them. The classrooms are fully equipped with age-appropriate Montessori materials and our outdoor area is their own free play, get together and use the half basketball court, or participate in other organized sporting activities.

detail: At Katy Kinder Prep we realize that each child has their own style of learning. No one method or purchased curriculum will be effective for all children.  We use the high reach curriculum as a tool, combined with state/national standards to prepare your child. We work to tailor learning activities that are based upon your child’s level and learning styles.We assess academics monthly to monitor progress and ensure growth.  But we know that we can’t do this alone. We need to partner with parents because we know that you are their most important teacher, and we want to support you in that role.

name: The Play Club Academy
detail: The Play Club Academy is a 24-hr. 7-day licensed child care center located in Houston, TX. We pride ourselves in being more than just a place for your child to sit for hours while you work or rest. It's one of many introductions to learning that your child will experience. The stepping stones your child will travel should lead to academic success before entering public or private school. At The Play Club Academy we take education and playtime seriously. Play. Work. Learn.™ These 3 words are so very important in every child's life. Play time is work and children learn best by doing. Our learning programs are not limited within our walls at the Academy. We take our classroom lessons and make them real through experiences. Last summer, we studied butterflies and the rain forest; our children visited the Museum of Science to experience a simulated rainforest with live butterflies. When the children studied wild & farm animals we took a tour of the zoo and the children wore masks to pretend to be the animals they studied. There's not enough space to share every thing we do & have done, but we'll try. Come on in an experience the phenomenon for yourself!

detail:
Head Start and Early Head Start helps to build a foundation for children's success.  Head Start/Early Head Start are comprehensive programs designed to foster the healthy development of young children from low-income families.  The programs have grown from a brief, eight-week summer program for preschoolers in 1965 to a year-round program today, serving children from birth to four and pregnant women.

The Head Start Bureau (HSB), the Administration on Children, Youth and Families (ACYF) Administration for Children and Families (ACF), and the Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS) administer the Head Start program.

name: Wooten YMCA
detail:
The YMCA of Austin offers afterschool care for children in grades K - 5 at fifteen licensed sites in three Austin area school districts. The Afterschool Care Program provides on-site care for your child, beginning when school is dismissed and continuing until 6:30 p.m.

Participating children learn valuable social and scholastic skills in a safe, fun, and supervised environment.

The afterschool care program offers a constructive balance of counselor led activities and free time for child exploration. Daily theme activities include arts and crafts, science/math activities, nutrition/wellness activities, presentation activities (music, theater, cooking, etc) and literacy. In addition, the Y delivers CATCH physical activity lessons daily and has made a commitment to meet the Y's Healthy Eating and Physical Activity Standards (HEPA). Lastly, there is always time for homework, a nutritious afternoon snack, and outside time on the playground.

name: Pre-K 4 SA - North Education Center
detail:
In 2011, Mayor Julián Castro convened a blue ribbon task-force of chief executive officers, superintendents, and education professionals to identify the most effective method for improving the quality of education in San Antonio. The Brainpower Taskforce recommended the development of a program focused on high-quality prekindergarten services for 4-year-old children.

Research shows high-quality prekindergarten has the most impact in improving overall education outcomes for a community and helps children to learn and read on grade-level, making them less likely to fall behind their classmates and more likely to graduate and attend college.

name: San Antonio Cottage Child Dev. Center
Sunshine Montessori Academy
detail:
The philosophy of Sunshine Montessori Academy is to encourage a childâ€™s interest and curiosity to learn and to develop as a responsible and independent thinker that will foster a life long love of learning.

Sunshine Montessori Academy has qualified Montessori Managing Director & trained staff by her, who takes a personal interest in their teaching and of the individual child. The staff at Sunshine Montessori Academy view education as much more than the training of minds. Their dedicated and caring ways help the child develop to be an intelligent, caring and loving human being.

The goal of Sunshine Montessori Academy is to educate the whole child through the Montessori approach which addresses the cognitive, social, emotional and physical needs of the young child.

Here at Sunshine Montessori Academy, we think that communication between parents and teachers is a vital component in providing an enriching and positive learning experience for the child's development.

Our students who attend Sunshine Montessori Academy are exposed to many academic subjects with ease and comfort. The materials offer the children experience with phonics, reading, writing, addition, subtraction, geometry, decimal system, geography, science and botany to name a few. Because of the excellent academics we offer, children usually perform to the traditional first and second grade levels when they leave our kindergarten program.

We have mixed age groups in all our class rooms. Each child is free to learn at his own level, pace and degree of interest. Younger and older children learn from each other. Each one is both a student and a teacher. Each Montessori material has a specific skill to develop, quality to demonstrate or fact to reveal. The children thrive in academics in these types of exciting learning atmosphere.

detail:
Little Saints Children’s Academy (LSCA), is a privately owned and operated child care facility dedicated to providing a quality program for children between the ages of six weeks and twelve years. We are a Christian-based center and pride ourselves on the good old Proverb 22:6.

We compellingly follow the guidelines of the Word of God, “we are to suffer little children to come unto Him for such is the Kingdom of Heaven.” Our goal is to provide love-n-care, a safe and Christian environment and support to every family. Little Saints Children’s Academy staff and administration believe that each child is a unique individual. Our programs and curriculum are designed to meet the developmental level of each child encouraging individuality and promoting self-confidence.

Bonafide staff – teachers, caregivers, and administrators help shower each child’s day to day involvement with the stimulus for creativity, encouraging participation, and fostering the values of respect, social responsibility, and personal identity. At the center, the child is given various opportunities and ways to acquire the skills s/he needs to build on the necessary know-how for overcoming developmental challenges ahead. Your child will be supervised in a guided facilitation process through play, individual, and group tasks.

Parents are privileged of our open-door policy, where they can witness their child be engaged in active learning at school. We hold an efficient child care security system using parent or guardian log-ins and visits oversight. Child pick ups are allowed only to individuals listed on the info provided by the parent/guardian as authorized. Otherwise, they must provide a signed letter or call for notification prior to the after school pick-up schedule.

Little Children’s Academy houses stimulating classrooms, interactive learning centers, and a wide playground where children can spend their time at some length of the day. Our infant room contains a diaper-changing station, a sink, and all necessary infant care contrivance to fully-provide the needs of your little one.

detail: Plantation Child Care and Development Center open its doors on December 4th, 2003. The center was designed and built with many innovative features for its time to ensure a “child friendly” environment.  The construction was and continues to be one of the largest in the area when it comes to child care and development centers spanning approximately 10,000 squared feet of construction strategically placed on a one acre lot in the tranquil and safe backset of Plantation Grove Blvd.  Each room is tailored to provide an appropriate learning environment with ample space for each child to develop according to their age.  From learning to nurturing, to health and safety, Plantation Child Care and Development Center offers many unique services. The center counts with amenities not found in typical centers such as art room, theater area, cooking center, library, computer lab, indoor and large shaded outdoor play areas and a “Mother’s Room” specifically built for mothers needing a quiet, private area to nurse their child. These programs served over 1,700 children in several schools and provided activities that support students’ emotional, social, physical, and intellectual development. Children enrolled in the programs demonstrated improved school attendance and academic performance over the long term, as verified by report cards.

For the school year 2013-2014, CIS-HOT launched its own independent afterschool program called “Play2Learn,” currently offered at two Waco ISD campuses: Provident Heights Elementary and Cedar Ridge Elementary. As with our previous successful afterschool programs, Play2Learn is designed to provide a safe and dynamic learning environment for the students and is run by caring adults. We provide help with homework, tutoring, various activities, and a light snack.

detail:

Services. Little Coconuts staff are all trained in CPR/First Aide. We provide breakfast, lunch and an afternoon snack. We are licensed to serve 45 children. 18 of the 45 spots are for infants ages newborn-18 months.

name: Bright Beginnings
detail:
Your child deserves the very best head start in life. Many young children begin attending primary school unprepared and apprehensive. Preschool is the best option to prepare your child for the road of education. We are Bright Beginnings Child Care Preschool and we are the best child care preschool service in Austin, TX. We are committed to providing all of our students with programs that will get them ready for public or private education systems.

The readiness of your child for school is as important to us as it is to you, so you can trust that we will do everything in our power to equip them with everything they will need to begin their education with success and confidence.

Our outstanding preschool program features age-appropriate curriculum designed to stimulate the minds of our students so that they can begin to develop reasoning and logic skills. Bright Beginnings Child Care Preschool encourages creativity and independence and we give all of our students special one-on-one care so every child feels as special as they should. Our preschool is not just a place where your child will be looked after while you are working, it is a place for your child to learn, grow, play, and develop critical social skills.

We encourage parents who are looking for a preschool and infant care program to come and visit our facilities. Talk with some of our teachers and caretakers and see why we are the best preschool program in the Austin area. Our program emphasizes individual care because we know every child is unique and deserves special attention. At the same time, we don’t neglect the importance of working and playing in a group setting.

name: Ecole Jean-Jacques Rousseau
detail:
Our mission is, in partnership with students, parents and staff to educate and encourage all students to reach their full potential and become successful contributors to society. In addition to excellent academics, our students speak two to three languages and are fully prepared for global multilingual world.

We look forward to continuing work on the priorities established the previous years in French, Mathematics, Earth and Life Science, Language Arts, World History, Geography and Latin. Technology, History of Arts, Visual Arts, and Foreign Language courses (Spanish and Arabic) are scheduled on weekly basis. We are especially pleased with our new science lab. Violin group lessons and private lessons are scheduled on different days depending on your child's schedule.

name: IDEA Austin YMCA
detail:
The YMCA of Austin offers afterschool care for children in grades K - 5 at fifteen licensed sites in three Austin area school districts. The Afterschool Care Program provides on-site care for your child, beginning when school is dismissed and continuing until 6:30 p.m.

Participating children learn valuable social and scholastic skills in a safe, fun, and supervised environment.

The afterschool care program offers a constructive balance of counselor led activities and free time for child exploration. Daily theme activities include arts and crafts, science/math activities, nutrition/wellness activities, presentation activities (music, theater, cooking, etc) and literacy. In addition, the Y delivers CATCH physical activity lessons daily and has made a commitment to meet the Y's Healthy Eating and Physical Activity Standards (HEPA). Lastly, there is always time for homework, a nutritious afternoon snack, and outside time on the playground. 

The end of each afterschool day will include Centers: Board Game Blvd., Hard Hat Highway (building), Craft Court (art), Drama Drive, and Literary Lane. 

Children are divided into age-appropriate groups for many of the daily activities. Special day-long programs, called All Day Cares, are available for most school holidays (see calendars below) and for all early release days. Care on these days is included with your monthly fees. As with all of our programs, the after school program emphasizes our five character values: respect, responsibility, honesty, faith, and caring. Additionally, after school curriculum is built on the Search Institute's 40 Developmental Assets.
